# Cursor Rules for paddy-glass

## Component Library

- **shadcn/ui** is the primary component library for this project
- Components are installed using: `npx shadcn@latest add [component-name]`
- Components are located in `@/components/ui`
- Always use shadcn/ui components when available instead of building custom components from scratch
- The project uses the "new-york" style variant
- Base color scheme: Neutral
- Icon library: Lucide React

## Project Structure

- Next.js 16 with App Router
- TypeScript with strict mode
- Tailwind CSS v4 for styling
- Components should be placed in `@/components/ui` (shadcn) or `@/components` (custom)
- Utilities are in `@/lib/utils` (includes the `cn()` helper for className merging)

## Styling Guidelines

- Use Tailwind CSS utility classes
- Use the `cn()` utility from `@/lib/utils` for conditional className merging
- Follow shadcn/ui design patterns and component APIs
- Support dark mode (CSS variables are already configured)

## Code Style

- Use TypeScript for all components
- Follow React 19 best practices
- Use functional components with proper TypeScript types
- Ensure components are accessible and follow shadcn/ui accessibility standards
